   "source": [
    "# 🦀 Day 2: Publishing to crates.io\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "Today we explore publishing your crate to **crates.io** — Rust's official package registry.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **What crates.io is**: The central registry for Rust packages\n",
    "- **Preparing for publish**: Cargo.toml metadata (description, license, repository, keywords, categories)\n",
    "- **Semantic versioning**: major.minor.patch\n",
    "- **`cargo package`** and **`cargo publish`**: Check and publish\n",
    "- **When NOT to publish**: Internal tools, learning projects"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cargo.toml metadata for publishing\n",
    "\n",
    "Required and recommended fields:\n",
    "- `name` — crate name (lowercase, hyphens)\n",
    "- `version` — semantic version (e.g., 0.1.0)\n",
    "- `description` — short summary (1–2 sentences)\n",
    "- `license` or `license-file` — e.g., MIT, Apache-2.0\n",
    "- `repository` — GitHub URL\n",
    "- `keywords` — up to 5 for discoverability\n",
    "- `categories` — up to 5 from crates.io list"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "// Example: well-configured Cargo.toml for publishing\n",
    "let toml_example = r##\"\n",
    "[package]\n",
    "name = \"rustkv\"\n",
    "version = \"0.1.0\"\n",
    "edition = \"2021\"\n",
    "description = \"A Redis-like key-value store written in Rust\"\n",
    "license = \"MIT\"\n",
    "repository = \"https://github.com/yourusername/rustkv\"\n",
    "keywords = [\"kv\", \"key-value\", \"redis\", \"storage\", \"database\"]\n",
    "categories = [\"database-implementations\", \"development-tools\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "[dependencies]\n",
    "tokio = { version = \"1\", features = [\"full\"] }\n",
    \"##;\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Cargo.toml for publishing:\");\n",
    "println!(\"{}\", toml_example);"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Publishing workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **`cargo package`** — Creates a tarball, checks what will be published (dry run)\n",
    "2. **`cargo publish --dry-run`** — Simulates publish without uploading\n",
    "3. **`cargo login`** — Authenticate with crates.io (paste API token from crates.io/settings/tokens)\n",
    "4. **`cargo publish`** — Upload to crates.io\n",
    "\n",
    "**Yanking**: `cargo yank --version 0.1.0` — prevents new dependencies but keeps existing ones working."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "// Semantic versioning: major.minor.patch\n",
    "// 0.1.0 -> 0.1.1: patch (bug fixes, no API change)\n",
    "// 0.1.1 -> 0.2.0: minor (new features, backward compatible)\n",
    "// 1.0.0 -> 2.0.0: major (breaking changes)\n",
    "\n",
    "fn version_display(major: u32, minor: u32, patch: u32) -> String {\n",
    "    format!(\"{}.{}.{}\", major, minor, patch)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Version: {}\", version_display(0, 1, 0));\n",
    "println!(\"Publishing best practices: CHANGELOG.md, minimal deps, good README\");"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📝 Exercise: Prepare your Cargo.toml for publishing\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Add `description`, `license`, `repository`, `keywords`, `categories`\n",
    "2. Run `cargo package` to verify\n",
    "3. Run `cargo publish --dry-run` (requires `cargo login` first)\n",
    "4. You don't have to actually publish — preparation is valuable practice!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🎯 Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "1. crates.io is Rust's package registry — publish with `cargo publish`\n",
    "2. Cargo.toml needs: description, license, repository, keywords, categories\n",
    "3. Semantic versioning: patch (fixes), minor (features), major (breaking)\n",
    "4. `cargo package` checks; `cargo yank` withdraws a version\n",
    "5. Don't publish internal tools or throwaway learning projects\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "**Tomorrow:** Open source contribution — finding projects"
   ]
  }
